WEBVTT

00:01.635 --> 00:03.820
Who is it this time,
Hap? I'm not an idiot.

00:03.822 --> 00:05.354
There's no one else but you.

00:05.423 --> 00:07.256
If I don't give these
people what they want,

00:07.325 --> 00:08.365
they're gonna kill my son.

00:08.426 --> 00:09.692
They're looking for oil.

00:09.761 --> 00:11.594
They won't have a clue that it's fake.

00:11.663 --> 00:12.562
Dr. Kipling: It's a boy.

00:12.630 --> 00:13.830
He's perfect.

00:13.898 --> 00:15.665
You thought Hap was your friend.

00:15.734 --> 00:17.834
He uses people to get information.

00:17.902 --> 00:18.837
- You're the one
- [Grunts]

00:18.861 --> 00:19.870
with a murder on your hands!

00:19.871 --> 00:21.571
I'll tell them you told
me to pull the trigger.

00:21.639 --> 00:23.473
That makes you as guilty as me.

00:23.541 --> 00:26.642
He told me he killed Spinks,
blamed him for the siphoning.

00:26.711 --> 00:28.511
- Testify to that?
- Absolutely.

00:28.580 --> 00:30.300
I'm worried about the
murder investigation.

00:30.348 --> 00:31.180
[Feedback]

00:31.249 --> 00:32.999
You're not alone, are
you? You're setting me up!

00:33.000 --> 00:34.383
I'll find you.

00:34.452 --> 00:35.918
No!

00:35.987 --> 00:37.458
No! No!

00:37.459 --> 00:38.521
[Grunts]

00:40.291 --> 00:41.357
Cody. Oh, my God.

00:41.426 --> 00:42.758
Call 911!

00:45.430 --> 00:49.465
♪

00:49.534 --> 00:52.902
♪ You got the potion,
yeah, you really do ♪

00:52.971 --> 00:55.838
I'm not ever gonna let
anything happen to you.

00:55.907 --> 00:57.340
You hear me?

00:57.408 --> 01:00.176
♪ Call me your lover,
call me another ♪

01:00.245 --> 01:01.677
<i>Woman: Code blue.</i>

01:01.746 --> 01:03.599
- Billy?
- [Sirens wailing]

01:03.681 --> 01:05.047
<i>- Code blue.
- What's happening?!</i>

01:05.116 --> 01:06.349
<i>Code blue.</i>

01:06.417 --> 01:09.152
<i>Paging Dr. Wolf to the O.R., stat.</i>

01:12.490 --> 01:14.290
<i>- Paging Dr. Wolf to the O.R., stat.
- Uh, excuse me, nurse?</i>

01:14.359 --> 01:16.030
I'm wondering about
my wife, Cody Lefever.

01:16.031 --> 01:18.394
- She's been in there for like three hours.
- She's still in surgery, sir.

01:18.463 --> 01:19.862
Yeah, look, is there, uh...

01:19.931 --> 01:21.611
is there anything you
can tell me, please?

01:21.666 --> 01:23.766
- She's in O.R. 2.
- Yeah.

01:23.835 --> 01:26.229
Tell me, how bad is it?

01:26.230 --> 01:27.670
I can tell you this.

01:27.939 --> 01:31.007
She's gonna get the finest
medical care there is.

01:31.075 --> 01:33.976
Carla and I chartered
a plane out of Aspen.

01:34.045 --> 01:37.513
We got the finest thoracic
surgeon there is in the country

01:37.582 --> 01:40.483
to roll his ass out of bed,
and he's in there with Cody now.

01:40.551 --> 01:42.752
[Sighing] Hap, I-I don't...

01:42.820 --> 01:44.687
I mean, I don't even
know what to say to you.

01:44.756 --> 01:46.622
You don't need to say anything, Billy.

01:46.691 --> 01:48.324
We're horrified by what happened.

01:48.393 --> 01:50.292
I mean, why would you...

01:50.361 --> 01:53.462
Listen, I may be a son
of a bitch in business.

01:53.531 --> 01:55.598
But when it comes to family...

01:55.666 --> 01:57.066
it's everything to me.

01:57.135 --> 01:59.168
I know you feel the same.

01:59.237 --> 02:01.827
<i>Transfusion team to O.R. 2, stat.</i>

02:02.140 --> 02:05.174
<i>- Transfusion team to O.R. 2, stat.
- O.R. 2. That's Cody's room.</i>

02:05.243 --> 02:06.609
Hey, hey, wait, wait.

02:06.677 --> 02:08.610
- Let them do their job, son.
- [Sighs]

02:08.679 --> 02:10.479
[Clears throat]

02:10.548 --> 02:12.314
Yeah, okay.

02:12.383 --> 02:14.116
Come on, sit down.

02:14.185 --> 02:16.085
All right.

02:19.190 --> 02:21.190
Are you sure I can't
get you a cup of coffee?

02:21.259 --> 02:22.339
Oh, no. I can't keep still.

02:22.393 --> 02:24.460
I have to do this, so thank you.

02:24.465 --> 02:26.265
Boy needs a shot of bourbon.

02:29.033 --> 02:31.500
[Sighs] I am so sorry.

02:31.569 --> 02:33.769
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:33.838 --> 02:35.104
How is she?

02:35.173 --> 02:36.573
You know, she's not doing too good.

02:36.641 --> 02:37.721
The attacker broke her rib,

02:37.775 --> 02:39.375
and it, uh, tore an artery in her chest,

02:39.444 --> 02:41.944
so they're just trying
to stop the bleeding.

02:42.013 --> 02:43.245
Oh, my God.

02:43.314 --> 02:45.614
Yeah, but, uh, Hap here
flew in a top surgeon,

02:45.683 --> 02:47.332
so she's in good hands at least.

02:47.333 --> 02:49.115
Very lucky to have friends
like the Briggs, eh?

02:49.120 --> 02:51.120
- Yeah.
- Come through when you need 'em.

02:52.223 --> 02:53.456
Where's Wick?

02:53.524 --> 02:55.057
Just parking the car.

02:55.126 --> 02:57.093
- Hey.
- Hey.

02:57.161 --> 02:58.360
Sorry about Cody, man.

02:58.429 --> 02:59.628
You holding up?

02:59.697 --> 03:01.430
Yeah, I'm trying, man.

03:01.499 --> 03:03.732
But, uh, I'm gonna go see
if the nurse has an update.

03:03.801 --> 03:05.601
Thank you, guys.

03:05.670 --> 03:06.936
Poor Billy.

03:07.004 --> 03:08.637
Well, I'm gonna get him a cup of coffee,

03:08.706 --> 03:10.106
even though he doesn't want one.

03:10.174 --> 03:10.906
You want anything?

03:10.975 --> 03:12.541
I'm good.

03:12.610 --> 03:14.743
It's gonna be a long day. [Sighs]

03:21.419 --> 03:24.854
[Siren wails in distance]

03:24.922 --> 03:27.289
Hey. You all right?

03:27.358 --> 03:30.548
Uh, yeah, yeah. Just...
worried about Cody.

03:32.063 --> 03:34.396
[Inhales deeply]

03:34.465 --> 03:37.326
Yeah. It's times like
these that remind you how...

03:38.302 --> 03:40.169
fragile life is...

03:40.238 --> 03:42.891
How the only thing that
really matters is...

03:43.591 --> 03:44.996
being with the one you love.

03:48.279 --> 03:49.712
Mm.

03:49.780 --> 03:52.648
- [Cellphone vibrating]
- Oh, hang on.

03:53.951 --> 03:56.218
That's the rig. I should take this.

03:56.487 --> 03:58.287
Hang on. Let me be where I can talk.

03:59.157 --> 04:00.456
[Door opens]

04:00.525 --> 04:01.590
Gary.

04:01.659 --> 04:03.325
You sold me out, you son of a bitch.

04:03.394 --> 04:05.161
That's not true, man,
okay, I would never do that.

04:05.229 --> 04:06.662
I heard the walkie.

04:06.731 --> 04:08.552
You lured me out so
the cops could jump me.

04:08.553 --> 04:10.666
Look, I don't know what you heard,
okay? But if the cops were there,

04:10.735 --> 04:12.434
then they were tracking
both of us, all right?

04:12.503 --> 04:13.802
That's the honest-to-God truth.

04:13.871 --> 04:16.238
Why does everything got to be
so complicated with you, man?

04:16.307 --> 04:17.973
If you'd have done what
you were supposed to do,

04:18.041 --> 04:19.541
I wouldn't have had to
do that job last night.

04:19.610 --> 04:21.844
What job?

04:21.913 --> 04:24.280
- Gary?
- I told you, I needed painkillers.

04:24.348 --> 04:26.203
My arm's broken. It's killing me!

04:28.085 --> 04:30.152
[Sighs]

04:30.221 --> 04:31.653
The pharmacy... that was you?

04:31.722 --> 04:33.756
Damn it, Gary. I know that girl.

04:33.824 --> 04:36.058
- She could die!
- Things got out of hand.

04:36.127 --> 04:38.160
It was supposed to be a
snatch-and-grab... simple.

04:38.229 --> 04:40.362
Just... just enough
to get me out of here.

04:40.431 --> 04:41.363
[Sighs]

04:41.432 --> 04:42.498
Wick?

04:42.567 --> 04:44.369
Yeah, okay. All right, just... [Sighs]

04:45.503 --> 04:46.503
Look, just calm down.

04:46.571 --> 04:48.304
We'll figure this out, all right?

04:48.372 --> 04:50.940
We'll find a way to get you out of town.

04:51.008 --> 04:52.008
For good.

04:53.778 --> 04:56.145
I was happy to get your call.

04:56.214 --> 04:58.380
Yeah, well...

04:58.449 --> 05:00.357
Sounded like Cody's
injuries were serious,

05:00.358 --> 05:02.176
and I knew you could help.

05:03.087 --> 05:05.588
Well, anyone that means
something to you, Jules,

05:05.656 --> 05:07.448
means something to me.

05:11.128 --> 05:12.361
[Laughing] What?

05:12.430 --> 05:14.597
You're always my knight in
shining bloody armor, eh?

05:14.665 --> 05:16.432
[Chuckles]

05:16.500 --> 05:19.911
- No matter how much I try to...
- So stop trying.

05:23.174 --> 05:25.808
I can't keep doing this, Hap.

05:25.876 --> 05:27.776
Just going round and round.

05:27.845 --> 05:29.712
Just tell me you don't miss me

05:29.780 --> 05:32.214
and I'll never bother you again.

05:32.283 --> 05:33.516
I don't miss you.

05:33.684 --> 05:36.252
I brought muffins. Anyone hungry?

05:36.320 --> 05:37.419
Starving.

05:37.488 --> 05:38.621
- How'd you know?
- [Magazine clatters]

05:38.689 --> 05:40.422
I always know what you need.

05:45.463 --> 05:46.362
[Laughs]

05:46.430 --> 05:48.063
Wick!

05:50.368 --> 05:52.401
Cassidy.

05:52.470 --> 05:53.736
You forgot already.

05:53.804 --> 05:54.804
Cassidy.

05:54.839 --> 05:56.171
Yes, of course.

05:56.240 --> 05:58.040
Uh, yeah. It's just been a while.

05:58.109 --> 05:59.908
17 months.

05:59.977 --> 06:01.277
But who's counting?

06:01.345 --> 06:02.778
[Chuckles]

06:02.847 --> 06:04.980
So, uh, what are you doing here?

06:05.049 --> 06:07.483
Oh, I'm visiting a friend in surgery.

06:07.551 --> 06:11.020
It's good to know you're
just as nice as I remember.

06:12.356 --> 06:13.956
I got to go. It's good seeing you.

06:14.025 --> 06:15.891
You too.

06:20.798 --> 06:22.665
- [Sighs]
- Any news?

06:22.733 --> 06:24.566
No. Uh, I don't
understand what's going on.

06:24.635 --> 06:26.268
It'll be okay. Cody's a fighter.

06:26.337 --> 06:28.003
Yeah.

06:28.072 --> 06:29.905
Mr. Lefever?

06:29.974 --> 06:31.807
Sir.

06:31.876 --> 06:33.208
[Clears throat]

06:33.277 --> 06:35.077
- Your wife's in recovery.
- Okay.

06:35.146 --> 06:37.780
I'm going to need to
monitor her for a few days.

06:37.848 --> 06:39.882
She and the baby are both fine.

06:39.950 --> 06:42.051
[Gasps] Kidding me?

06:42.119 --> 06:43.752
Doctor, thank you so much!

06:43.821 --> 06:46.488
[Monitor beeping]

06:53.597 --> 06:56.298
Hey, baby, it's me.

06:56.367 --> 06:58.867
You're doing great.
The baby's doing great.

07:00.237 --> 07:01.704
Cody: Hi.

07:03.240 --> 07:06.875
I guess I got my house
party, just not in the house.

07:08.279 --> 07:10.979
We're gonna find the
monster that did this to you.

07:12.883 --> 07:15.084
- Did you get a look at him?
- Not right now, Hap.

07:15.152 --> 07:18.120
No, no, it's okay.
Cody, did you see him?

07:19.390 --> 07:21.390
Yeah, I did.

07:23.627 --> 07:25.343
I saw his face.

