- _
- [Lacey scoffs]

07:47.714 --> 07:48.980
Really?

07:51.351 --> 07:52.511
[Scoffs]

07:54.855 --> 07:56.671
<i>It's A.J. leave a message.</i>

07:58.125 --> 07:59.925
Flowers and a card?

07:59.993 --> 08:01.459
Really?

08:01.528 --> 08:04.763
God, you apologize worse than you spy.

08:04.832 --> 08:06.398
[Cellphone beeps]

08:12.372 --> 08:13.772
[Sighs]

08:13.841 --> 08:16.209
I find the innocence of
children so refreshing.

08:16.210 --> 08:17.510
Don't you?

08:18.278 --> 08:20.558
Your son's work shows real promise.

08:24.484 --> 08:26.418
Wish I could say the same for yours.

08:26.486 --> 08:28.453
What are you talking
about? I did what you asked.

08:28.522 --> 08:30.488
I brought you Hap Briggs' USGS report.

08:30.557 --> 08:32.357
Too bad you didn't get me the real one.

08:32.426 --> 08:34.491
According to that report,

08:34.561 --> 08:38.230
the McCutching land has
less oil than a Gulf station.

08:38.298 --> 08:41.799
Yet Hap Briggs is sinking
wells, preparing to drill.

08:41.868 --> 08:44.135
Does that sound like Hap Briggs to you?

08:44.203 --> 08:46.638
The report can't be trusted.

08:46.707 --> 08:48.072
Maybe neither can you.

08:48.141 --> 08:49.841
Look, my mission was
to bring you the report.

08:49.910 --> 08:51.394
I can't be held responsible

08:51.395 --> 08:54.623
- for whatever's in it, but...
- Ahmed, this petulance is unbecoming.

08:55.515 --> 08:56.948
Your job is now simple.

08:57.017 --> 08:58.984
Get me the real report.

08:59.052 --> 09:00.970
You've got 36 hours.

09:02.022 --> 09:04.856
[Children laughing]

09:04.925 --> 09:07.702
Because we all want to see
our children grow up, don't we?

09:08.395 --> 09:11.429
♪

09:16.637 --> 09:18.251
<i>Dr. Harper to I.C.U.</i>

09:18.252 --> 09:19.589
<i>- Dr. Harper to I.C.U.
- [Sighs]</i>

09:19.590 --> 09:21.570
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:21.594 --> 09:22.775
[Chuckles nervously]

09:22.776 --> 09:24.542
Ah, that's a lucky boy of yours.

09:24.611 --> 09:28.213
No, this is actually for Cody,
you know, when she, uh, wakes up.

09:28.282 --> 09:31.216
Hey, uh, listen, I, uh...

09:31.285 --> 09:34.486
I just wanted to really thank
you for bringing in that surgeon.

09:34.554 --> 09:36.922
I care about Cody, too.

09:36.990 --> 09:39.925
[Chuckles] She's quite a
spitfire, that wife of yours.

09:39.993 --> 09:43.728
I knew it the minute she
outfoxed us on McCutching.

09:43.797 --> 09:45.330
Yeah, well, the nurses said that

09:45.399 --> 09:47.466
the, uh, doc pretty much saved her life.

09:47.734 --> 09:49.267
Yeah.

09:49.336 --> 09:51.670
So, um, look, if there's
anything that I can do,

09:51.738 --> 09:54.205
I will do anything to repay you.

09:54.274 --> 09:56.374
Come work for me.

09:56.443 --> 09:58.243
What? Come work for you?

09:58.312 --> 10:00.288
After everything that
went down between us?

10:00.289 --> 10:01.980
Well, actually, it's...

10:02.049 --> 10:03.915
because of how it went down.

10:03.984 --> 10:06.985
Billy, you got a wildcatter streak.

10:07.054 --> 10:09.854
I think you'd be a real
asset for Briggs Oil.

10:09.923 --> 10:12.924
- And what? Stringing pipe or...
- No, sir.

10:12.993 --> 10:15.860
Doing land deals in the front office.

10:15.929 --> 10:17.562
I'm about to... [Sighs]

10:17.631 --> 10:19.893
get into the biggest play of my life.

10:21.301 --> 10:22.667
And every drilling outfit in the world

10:22.736 --> 10:25.032
is gonna be nipping at my heels.

10:27.274 --> 10:29.274
I could really use your help.

10:29.343 --> 10:31.176
[Clears throat] Hap, I... [Chuckles]

10:31.244 --> 10:32.811
Don't answer now.

10:32.879 --> 10:35.413
Take care of Cody and that baby, and...

10:35.482 --> 10:37.749
think about it and call me next week.

10:37.818 --> 10:40.518
I will do that. And, hey, thank you.

10:40.587 --> 10:41.587
<i>...2217.</i>

10:41.621 --> 10:44.656
<i>Dr. Borne, extension 2217.</i>

10:44.725 --> 10:46.424
[Telephone rings]

10:46.493 --> 10:48.893
[Footsteps departing]

10:50.530 --> 10:51.896
Wick: She can identify you!

10:51.965 --> 10:53.665
That's attempted murder on top of

10:53.734 --> 10:55.367
what you already did to Spinks!

10:55.435 --> 10:58.703
The sheriff is gonna
call in the state police.

10:58.772 --> 11:00.305
That means a manhunt.

11:00.374 --> 11:02.007
A manhunt!

11:02.075 --> 11:03.875
You know how long it's
gonna take them to figure out

11:03.944 --> 11:06.344
that your granny's got a cabin
10 miles out of town, huh?

11:06.613 --> 11:09.254
Well, I ain't going anywhere till
I get some pills and some cash.

11:09.282 --> 11:11.049
Gary, you're not getting it!

11:11.118 --> 11:14.386
One word... one word from
Cody, and they're all over you!

11:14.454 --> 11:15.854
All over us.

11:15.922 --> 11:17.355
We're in this together,

11:17.424 --> 11:18.990
and in case you're having
trouble remembering that...

11:19.059 --> 11:20.525
<i>- [Beep]
- Wick: Hey, you're the one</i>

11:20.594 --> 11:22.194
<i>who upped it from grand theft to murder.</i>

11:22.229 --> 11:23.762
<i>Gary: Spinks was gonna turn us in.</i>

11:23.830 --> 11:25.697
I got plenty more.

11:25.766 --> 11:28.466
So you better get me
some pills and some cash

11:28.535 --> 11:31.536
'cause if I go down, you go down.

11:31.605 --> 11:33.271
Full stop!

11:33.340 --> 11:35.006
♪

11:35.075 --> 11:36.975
[Maggie Eckford's "Give it to Me" plays]

11:37.044 --> 11:39.944
♪ You know I've got to have it ♪

11:40.013 --> 11:42.714
♪ I'm gonna take what's mine ♪

11:42.783 --> 11:45.517
♪ 'Cause I crave a little danger ♪

11:45.585 --> 11:48.086
♪ To keep the rush alive ♪

11:48.155 --> 11:51.156
♪ I won't take no for an answer ♪

11:51.224 --> 11:53.925
♪ I ain't backing down ♪

11:53.994 --> 11:56.861
♪ It drives me a little crazy ♪

11:56.930 --> 11:58.296
♪ I gotta have it now ♪

11:58.365 --> 12:00.565
♪ So give it to me ♪

12:04.471 --> 12:06.504
♪ Give it to me ♪

12:09.709 --> 12:12.077
♪ Come on, give it to me ♪

12:16.450 --> 12:18.350
Hey, now.

12:18.718 --> 12:19.718
Look at you.

12:19.753 --> 12:20.919
[Chuckles]

12:20.987 --> 12:22.887
You could still walk
any runway in the world

12:22.956 --> 12:24.589
and turn every head.

12:24.658 --> 12:26.991
Big meeting on a new play today.

12:27.060 --> 12:29.127
Need backup?

12:30.464 --> 12:33.098
You have enough to do.

12:33.166 --> 12:35.066
I can handle this.

12:38.071 --> 12:40.305
♪

12:40.373 --> 12:42.173
[Knock on door]

12:46.613 --> 12:48.780
Carla.

12:52.886 --> 12:54.486
Come on in.

12:54.554 --> 12:57.632
<i>Respiratory therapist to I.C.U.</i>

12:58.138 --> 13:00.528
<i>Respiratory therapist to I.C.U.</i>

13:03.063 --> 13:04.395
Emma, hey.

13:04.464 --> 13:05.997
How you doing? How's,
uh... how's Clifton?

13:06.066 --> 13:08.099
- Better.
- Yes, good.

13:08.168 --> 13:09.834
Your wife?

13:09.903 --> 13:11.202
She's doing okay.

13:11.271 --> 13:13.505
A long night, but, uh,
things are looking up.

13:13.573 --> 13:15.240
Why is that?

13:15.308 --> 13:17.942
'Cause Hap Briggs offered you a job?

13:19.412 --> 13:22.213
I overheard you talking earlier.

13:22.282 --> 13:24.182
Don't you see what he's doing?

13:24.251 --> 13:25.583
He's taking advantage of your situation

13:25.652 --> 13:26.684
to reel you back in.

13:26.753 --> 13:28.086
Yeah, well, if it wasn't for Hap,

13:28.155 --> 13:29.721
Cody might not have pulled through.

13:29.789 --> 13:31.289
You don't get it.

13:31.358 --> 13:33.358
You scared him, Billy.

13:33.426 --> 13:34.592
He knows that you can beat him,

13:34.661 --> 13:36.394
and what does Hap do
when something scares him?

13:36.463 --> 13:37.695
He buys it.

13:37.764 --> 13:38.963
I think you're being a
little dramatic right n...

13:39.032 --> 13:40.672
The devil doesn't come
at you with a pitchfork.

13:40.673 --> 13:42.185
He helps you when you're down,

13:42.186 --> 13:43.501
and then he sucks you
in with empty promises

13:43.570 --> 13:44.769
until he destroys you.

13:44.838 --> 13:46.571
Okay, look, I appreciate
your concern right now, Emma.

13:46.640 --> 13:47.672
I really do.

13:47.741 --> 13:49.040
But taking care of my wife and the baby

13:49.109 --> 13:50.842
is all that matters to me.

13:54.314 --> 13:58.049
As much as I'm enjoying
our little visit...

13:58.118 --> 14:00.051
I am kind of wondering why you're here.

14:02.589 --> 14:03.589
Does he love you?

14:03.623 --> 14:05.390
Who?

14:05.458 --> 14:07.091
My husband.

14:07.160 --> 14:09.894
Uh [Chuckles nervously]

14:09.963 --> 14:10.839
Carla, I've got no idea

14:10.863 --> 14:13.423
- what you're going on about.
- Jules, I saw you at the hospital.

14:14.634 --> 14:16.067
I know how Hap looks at something

14:16.136 --> 14:18.036
he thinks belongs to him.

14:20.707 --> 14:21.773
- [Cork pops]
- So...

14:23.710 --> 14:25.343
...does he love you?

14:27.180 --> 14:29.914
He did.

14:29.983 --> 14:31.349
Years ago.

14:31.418 --> 14:34.118
Before he met you.

14:34.187 --> 14:35.620
And now?

14:35.689 --> 14:37.755
It's over.

14:44.764 --> 14:47.098
Look at all you've accomplished, Jules,

14:47.167 --> 14:49.244
in business and in life.

14:54.374 --> 14:56.241
I just wonder what could make you choose

14:56.310 --> 14:57.575
to be the other woman...

14:57.944 --> 15:01.179
With a man we both know
grows bored very quickly.

15:01.248 --> 15:03.548
I told you, I ended it with Hap.

15:03.617 --> 15:05.984
Then you need to be more convincing.

15:06.052 --> 15:08.886
My husband needs to
know that his only option

15:08.955 --> 15:10.421
is to be done with you.

15:10.490 --> 15:13.291
I'm sure you can be very persuasive

15:13.360 --> 15:14.692
when you want to be.

15:18.031 --> 15:22.467
- And for Wick's sake, I hope I'm right.
- You wouldn't dare tell Wick.

15:22.535 --> 15:25.870
Maybe over breakfast or over dinner,

15:25.939 --> 15:28.533
but however it's done, yes.

15:31.878 --> 15:34.145
And it will destroy him.

15:42.389 --> 15:44.188
[Glass clatters]

15:45.859 --> 15:47.475
Thanks for the wine.

15:48.528 --> 15:50.695
[Door opens, closes]

15:51.642 --> 15:52.732
Here, drink this.

15:53.058 --> 15:54.892
- It'll make you feel better.
- [Chuckles]

15:54.960 --> 15:57.731
Yeah, I'll feel better when you
give them the real USGS survey,

15:57.796 --> 15:59.796
but we know that's not gonna happen.

15:59.865 --> 16:02.265
[Chuckles] No, that's not happening.

16:02.334 --> 16:05.669
The real report shows that
McCutching sits at the gateway

16:05.737 --> 16:07.998
to oil reserves that are...

16:08.707 --> 16:12.075
twice the size of the oil
reserves in the Middle East.

16:12.144 --> 16:16.146
That's like saying Hap Briggs
has the keys to the U.S. mint.

16:16.215 --> 16:18.648
And if they know that,
they'll try and stop me.

16:18.717 --> 16:20.083
Yeah, or take it for themselves.

16:20.152 --> 16:22.305
- Hmm.
- They've been after the mother lode

16:22.306 --> 16:23.247
since the boom started.

16:23.248 --> 16:24.916
Yeah, which is how
we got stuck with you.

16:25.190 --> 16:26.656
I'm guessing.

16:26.725 --> 16:28.892
All right, so, here's what we got to do.

16:28.961 --> 16:31.561
We need to make them think that
what I'm really drilling for

16:31.630 --> 16:33.930
is not oil, but natural gas.

16:33.999 --> 16:36.233
Natural gas... that way, it
wouldn't appear on the survey.

16:36.301 --> 16:39.169
And they'll think the survey
they have is the real one.

16:39.238 --> 16:40.112
Mm.

16:40.136 --> 16:42.808
I'm gonna need you guys to
mock up some geo reports,

16:42.809 --> 16:45.575
some new satellite images,
internal docs on McCutching.

16:45.644 --> 16:47.444
- Yeah, I can do that myself.
- I can do that.

16:49.047 --> 16:52.994
O-okay, so, look... [Sighs]
I don't know what's going on.

16:52.995 --> 16:54.888
- Oh, nothing's going on.
- Nothing's going...

16:56.121 --> 16:57.787
Okay, I lied.

16:57.856 --> 16:59.860
I know everything that's
going on with the two of you,

16:59.861 --> 17:01.162
but I don't care.

17:01.163 --> 17:03.560
In order for this to get
done in a timely manner,

17:03.629 --> 17:05.560
I need you to work together.

17:05.630 --> 17:07.329
So figure it out.

17:10.301 --> 17:12.234
[Sighs]

17:20.279 --> 17:22.378
I got as much as I could.

17:22.446 --> 17:25.781
It's crazy how I'll
still do whatever you ask.

17:26.151 --> 17:27.185
Yeah.

17:28.020 --> 17:30.220
Why do you need those anyway?

17:30.289 --> 17:32.322
Oh, I'm just in the
mood to party, you know?

17:32.391 --> 17:33.990
So, you'll call me then, right?

17:34.059 --> 17:35.825
Yeah, of course.

17:35.894 --> 17:38.495
♪

17:52.244 --> 17:53.843
I will make this right.

17:53.912 --> 17:56.412
Meantime, as soon as the doctor
says your wife is strong enough...

17:56.448 --> 17:58.348
- [Cellphone vibrating]
- ...we'll show her a lineup of mug shots,

17:58.417 --> 18:01.818
- some local persons of interest.
- Billy: Not until she's ready, Sheriff.

18:01.887 --> 18:04.154
No problem. We'll take
it from there, okay?

18:04.522 --> 18:06.055
Wick?

18:07.426 --> 18:09.259
Sheriff.

18:09.328 --> 18:10.593
Billy.

18:10.662 --> 18:12.729
I was just coming to
check on the patient.

18:12.798 --> 18:15.131
Yeah, the doctor said she's
getting stronger, so...

18:15.200 --> 18:19.002
I see your friend, uh,
Laframboise is still missing.

18:19.071 --> 18:22.272
But he hasn't contacted you, huh?

18:22.341 --> 18:23.973
No. No.

18:24.042 --> 18:27.110
No, he hasn't, but if he does,
you're my first call, obviously.

18:27.179 --> 18:30.046
Would you excuse us
one second? Hey, Wick.

18:30.115 --> 18:33.116
[Woman speaking indistinctly over P.A.]

18:34.353 --> 18:36.586
Know this... that, um...

18:36.655 --> 18:38.288
The longer he's out there,

18:38.356 --> 18:40.857
the more dangerous
this is for everybody.

18:40.926 --> 18:43.493
Yeah, of course.

18:44.262 --> 18:45.622
Mr. Lefever.

18:45.931 --> 18:47.564
Thanks. I'll talk to you soon.

18:47.632 --> 18:48.648
Thank you, Sheriff.

18:48.672 --> 18:49.700
- All right.
- Yeah.

18:49.701 --> 18:51.434
- Wick.
- [Sighs]

18:53.505 --> 18:54.671
What was that about?

18:54.739 --> 18:56.506
Ah, nothing, just some
guy I used to know.

18:56.575 --> 18:59.576
Listen, uh, what your dad did for us

18:59.644 --> 19:01.945
was, uh, really cool.

19:02.013 --> 19:04.314
Maybe I was too quick
to judge, you know?

19:05.784 --> 19:07.784
No, you were right to judge me.

19:07.852 --> 19:10.119
- I'm an ass.
- [Chuckles]

19:10.188 --> 19:12.957
Well, hey, I'm gonna be outside
getting some air if you want to join.

19:16.194 --> 19:17.694
Yeah, sure.

19:18.263 --> 19:19.562
[Unscrews flask]

19:20.632 --> 19:21.664
[Chuckles]

19:21.733 --> 19:24.500
You, uh... you always travel with this?

19:24.569 --> 19:26.769
It helps when your
old man is Hap Briggs.

19:26.838 --> 19:29.606
[Chuckles] Yeah. I bet.

19:31.076 --> 19:33.209
I got to say...

19:33.278 --> 19:35.154
You're handling this like a champ.

19:36.848 --> 19:38.443
When Cody was in surgery...

19:39.718 --> 19:42.852
All I could think about was
just beating the living hell

19:42.921 --> 19:44.854
out of that scumbag
who tried to hurt her.

19:44.923 --> 19:46.723
And now?

19:46.791 --> 19:48.691
Now all I can think
about is how lucky we are.

19:48.760 --> 19:50.660
You know, I mean...

19:50.729 --> 19:55.565
That whole deal could've
gone... real different.

19:55.634 --> 19:58.668
And I wouldn't even
recognize my life right now.

20:02.240 --> 20:03.525
Up here...

20:04.743 --> 20:06.978
there's a fine line between...

20:07.579 --> 20:09.512
Well, most things, really.

20:09.581 --> 20:11.047
Hmm.

20:11.116 --> 20:13.144
Rich and poor, right and wrong...

20:14.419 --> 20:15.885
dead or alive.

20:15.954 --> 20:17.220
Mm.

20:17.288 --> 20:19.255
Yeah.

20:19.324 --> 20:21.357
It's just crazy how one
man could have destroyed

20:21.426 --> 20:23.726
everything I care about.

20:23.995 --> 20:26.118
You know what the scariest thing is?

20:29.034 --> 20:32.201
There's not a damn thing
I could do about it.

20:35.907 --> 20:38.474
Yeah, there's nothing worse
than feeling that vulnerable.

20:40.912 --> 20:42.682
I know what it's like to have...

20:43.748 --> 20:45.815
someone hold your fate in their hands.

20:48.086 --> 20:50.353
Yeah, well, hey, thanks for the drink.

20:50.422 --> 20:51.854
Yeah.

20:51.923 --> 20:54.691
♪

20:59.664 --> 21:02.432
<i>Trauma team, extension 2561.</i>

21:02.500 --> 21:05.168
<i>- [Beeping]
- Trauma team, extension 2561.</i>

21:05.236 --> 21:07.503
<i>Her B.P.'S 80/50 and dropping.</i>

21:07.572 --> 21:09.172
[Indistinct shouting]

21:09.740 --> 21:10.874
We got to go!

21:11.242 --> 21:13.309
<i>- [Beeping continues]
- Someone call up...</i>

21:13.378 --> 21:14.777
How far was she?

21:14.846 --> 21:17.236
Nurse: I think she's just
finishing out her first trimester.

21:17.449 --> 21:18.281
Call the blood bank.

21:18.350 --> 21:20.087
Let them know we need
at least three units.

21:20.885 --> 21:22.685
[Speaks indistinctly]

21:22.754 --> 21:24.153
Somebody open her I.V.

21:24.222 --> 21:26.489
Hey, hey. Cody? Where
are you taking her to?

21:26.558 --> 21:27.857
- Please, sir, she's in good hands.
- What's happening?!

21:27.858 --> 21:29.024
Where is she going?!
Where are you taking her?!

21:29.160 --> 21:30.827
Cody!

21:36.118 --> 21:38.852
Billy: I'm just happy that you're safe.

21:38.921 --> 21:41.888
I thought I lost you.

21:41.957 --> 21:45.025
[Sniffles] This place...

21:45.094 --> 21:46.793
[Sighs]

21:46.862 --> 21:50.377
I knew it would be hard to
come here and start over.

21:53.969 --> 21:55.035
[Sighs]

21:55.104 --> 21:57.051
Losing the baby is too much.

21:58.540 --> 21:59.644
Hey.

22:00.709 --> 22:02.841
We will start over.

22:04.446 --> 22:06.138
And we will have a family.

22:07.182 --> 22:08.982
[Sniffles]

22:09.051 --> 22:10.566
Promise.

22:15.591 --> 22:18.231
Hey, Lace. This a bad time?

22:19.161 --> 22:20.570
For you?

22:21.830 --> 22:23.053
Never.

22:26.101 --> 22:27.634
You okay?

22:29.505 --> 22:31.131
I want to ask you something.

22:33.242 --> 22:35.417
- And I want you to be honest.
- Hm?

22:36.445 --> 22:38.206
Am I a good person?

22:39.548 --> 22:41.000
Yes.

22:41.850 --> 22:43.450
Of course.

22:43.519 --> 22:44.684
[Sighs]

22:44.753 --> 22:45.974
Where's this coming from?

22:47.456 --> 22:50.594
My whole life, I've made
every bad choice possible.

22:52.015 --> 22:55.362
I've screwed up every opportunity
anyone's ever given me.

22:55.430 --> 22:56.563
Yeah, no, stop.

22:56.632 --> 22:59.650
Wick, I am not gonna listen to this.

23:01.637 --> 23:04.538
You are way too hard on yourself.

23:04.606 --> 23:06.276
You are.

23:07.476 --> 23:09.643
[Sniffles]

23:09.911 --> 23:11.447
I mean, come on.

23:12.381 --> 23:15.079
Tell me, what have
you done that's so bad?

23:15.551 --> 23:18.218
Lace, what if I could do one thing?

23:18.287 --> 23:21.188
Just one thing... one
little thing that would...

23:21.256 --> 23:23.302
put all this bad stuff behind me?

23:24.026 --> 23:25.634
I could have a fresh start...

23:27.863 --> 23:29.593
as the man I know I can be.

23:30.399 --> 23:32.855
You're scaring me a little, Wick.

23:35.003 --> 23:37.184
What exactly are you planning?

23:45.480 --> 23:46.724
Nothing.

23:47.683 --> 23:49.483
I'm just... I'm talking.

23:49.551 --> 23:50.706
[Chuckles] You know me.

23:53.088 --> 23:54.156
Wick.

23:55.224 --> 23:56.590
[Sighs]

23:58.327 --> 24:00.927
If you need anything...

24:00.996 --> 24:02.500
I'm here.

24:03.232 --> 24:04.297
You know that?

24:04.366 --> 24:05.458
Yeah.

24:06.368 --> 24:08.515
You're my first and last call, always.

24:12.040 --> 24:14.040
Now, Mrs. Lefever, are you sure

24:14.109 --> 24:16.209
you're up to doing this right now?

24:16.278 --> 24:19.112
It's Cody. I'm sure.

24:19.181 --> 24:21.147
'Cause if you're not,
look, you don't have to.

24:21.216 --> 24:23.250
I'm fine, Billy.

24:23.318 --> 24:25.252
This man can't get away.

24:25.320 --> 24:27.220
- [Sniffles]
- Okay.

24:27.289 --> 24:28.330
Cody...

24:29.658 --> 24:31.525
These are men who match the description

24:31.593 --> 24:33.499
eyewitnesses gave to us.

24:37.232 --> 24:38.331
That's him.

24:38.400 --> 24:39.933
- Which one?
- That one.

24:40.002 --> 24:40.867
You sure?

24:40.936 --> 24:43.313
Absolutely, yeah. His mask came off.

24:44.239 --> 24:45.672
I pulled it off.

24:46.608 --> 24:48.475
What's his name, Sheriff?

24:48.543 --> 24:50.877
Gary Laframboise.

24:56.885 --> 24:58.351
[Computer keys clacking]

24:58.420 --> 25:00.887
[Sighs]

25:00.956 --> 25:01.956
[Stammering] I-if...

25:01.990 --> 25:04.858
Can you stop breathing down my neck?

25:04.926 --> 25:06.103
- Well, you know...
- Literally,

25:06.104 --> 25:07.535
- you're breathing down my neck.
- Yeah, there's an easier way...

25:07.536 --> 25:09.763
There's an easier way to convert
crude oil into natural gas.

25:09.831 --> 25:11.498
- All you have to do is multiply the...
- Okay, no offense.

25:11.566 --> 25:14.119
Listen, I am Hap Briggs'
daughter, all right?

25:14.135 --> 25:16.670
This isn't the first
time I'm tweaking a geo.

25:16.738 --> 25:18.405
All right, okay, I get it.

25:18.473 --> 25:20.240
You hate me.

25:20.309 --> 25:21.875
I'm a bad boyfriend and a worse spy,

25:21.943 --> 25:23.877
but the Saudis put me
here because I know oil.

25:23.945 --> 25:25.178
Not because you're James Bond?

25:25.247 --> 25:26.780
[Chuckles]

25:26.848 --> 25:30.483
Look, I have a PhD in geophysics
and petroleum engineering.

25:31.586 --> 25:33.453
That's why they chose me.

25:33.522 --> 25:35.555
So, yeah, just hand over the keyboard,

25:35.624 --> 25:36.984
and I'll do what I know how to do.

25:39.361 --> 25:41.027
You know what?

25:41.096 --> 25:42.242
Have at it.

25:43.198 --> 25:44.483
All right.

25:51.473 --> 25:55.709
Okay, so, you know a little
something about cycloalkenes.

25:55.777 --> 25:57.510
Well, this...

25:57.579 --> 26:00.413
along with the REGDEX filing
and the equipment inventory...

26:00.482 --> 26:01.715
Which I got for you.

26:01.783 --> 26:04.007
...should prove to my people
that the survey is legit.

26:06.188 --> 26:07.426
And so am I.

26:07.956 --> 26:09.856
[Chuckles]

26:09.925 --> 26:11.524
You see?

26:11.593 --> 26:14.294
We can actually do some
good when we're not fighting.

26:16.798 --> 26:18.498
Like keeping my son safe.

26:18.567 --> 26:21.167
♪

26:24.072 --> 26:26.016
I can't believe I'm about to ask this.

26:27.509 --> 26:30.219
Your son's mother...

26:32.948 --> 26:36.116
Are you two...

26:36.184 --> 26:39.025
[Sighs] She's... She's my wife.

26:40.088 --> 26:41.722
[Sighs] Of course.

26:42.290 --> 26:44.190
You're a spy.

26:44.259 --> 26:45.859
You're married.

26:45.927 --> 26:47.827
A-anything else while we're sharing?

26:47.896 --> 26:50.157
Divorce is complicated in Saudi Arabia.

26:50.158 --> 26:51.965
We knew a long time ago

26:52.033 --> 26:54.183
we just weren't right for each other.

26:58.507 --> 27:01.241
♪ Start the engine ♪

27:01.309 --> 27:02.718
She's just not you.

27:04.613 --> 27:07.747
♪ Hear it turning ♪

27:10.552 --> 27:15.588
♪ God only knows how far you'll go ♪

27:22.097 --> 27:24.764
- ♪ Slow down ♪
- [Sighs] You have to go.

27:24.833 --> 27:28.868
♪ Let it catch up to you now ♪

27:28.937 --> 27:30.203
You're gonna be late.

27:32.707 --> 27:33.707
All right.

27:33.742 --> 27:36.843
♪ Slow down ♪

27:36.912 --> 27:42.849
♪ Let it catch up to you now ♪

27:42.918 --> 27:44.417
<i>Gary: It's Gary again.</i>

27:44.486 --> 27:46.286
<i>Here's what I don't understand.</i>

27:46.354 --> 27:48.188
<i>Why am I always having to call you?</i>

27:48.256 --> 27:50.557
<i>You should've been back here by now.</i>

27:50.625 --> 27:53.193
<i>I swear, man, you do me dirty on this...</i>

27:53.261 --> 27:56.062
<i>Remember, Spinks and I
used to be tight, too,</i>

27:56.131 --> 27:58.023
<i>and look what happened to him.</i>

27:59.234 --> 28:00.633
<i>So get here fast,</i>

28:00.702 --> 28:04.020
<i>because if I go down, I ain't
going down alone, partner.</i>

28:07.175 --> 28:08.475
Where is he?

28:08.543 --> 28:10.276
- Who?
- Gary... your old buddy Gary.

28:10.345 --> 28:11.978
He's the one who attacked Cody.

28:12.047 --> 28:13.413
[Sighs]

28:14.850 --> 28:16.015
I know.

28:16.084 --> 28:18.117
What do you mean you know, huh?

28:18.186 --> 28:21.621
What do you mean you know?!
He killed my son, Wick!

28:21.690 --> 28:22.956
You have every right to be upset.

28:23.025 --> 28:24.691
That guy is a bad dude, trust me.

28:24.759 --> 28:26.192
- What's that mean?!
- It doesn't matter!

28:26.261 --> 28:27.327
All you need to know is,

28:27.328 --> 28:28.928
you do not want to
get mixed up with him.

28:29.097 --> 28:31.431
[Breathing heavily]

28:31.500 --> 28:33.066
[Sighs]

28:33.134 --> 28:34.767
And you swear to me...

28:34.836 --> 28:36.970
you swear to me you
don't know where he is.

28:37.038 --> 28:38.238
What if I did?

28:38.306 --> 28:40.039
What are you gonna do?
You gonna kick his ass?

28:40.108 --> 28:42.360
- You gonna go put a bullet in him?
- [Sighs]

28:42.411 --> 28:44.511
Billy, you are walking
that fine line right now.

28:44.579 --> 28:47.680
Don't let a scumbag
like Gary push you over.

28:47.749 --> 28:49.349
It's a really easy line to cross,

28:49.417 --> 28:51.451
but it's a hell of a
lot harder to get back.

28:52.521 --> 28:54.187
Yeah, well, you're crazy

28:54.256 --> 28:55.522
if you think I'm gonna let this go.

28:55.590 --> 28:57.390
I think you should go
take care of your wife,

28:57.425 --> 28:59.225
thank God for answering
most of your prayers,

28:59.294 --> 29:01.895
- and let me take care of this, okay?
- Oh, let you take care of this?

29:01.896 --> 29:03.162
Yes.

29:03.298 --> 29:04.464
Billy.

29:04.533 --> 29:06.032
[Door closes]

29:16.336 --> 29:17.828
<i>Hap: It made me think of you.</i>

29:18.772 --> 29:19.864
<i>Jules: A sea flower.</i>

29:19.865 --> 29:21.732
<i>- Hap: Your favorite.
- Jules: Mm-hmm.</i>

29:27.506 --> 29:29.768
<i>We can't keep doing this, Hap.</i>

29:33.545 --> 29:35.062
<i>Just tell me you don't miss me.</i>

29:37.983 --> 29:39.216
Aah!

29:58.704 --> 30:00.504
Oh, damn it, Wick.

30:12.785 --> 30:14.584
[Dialing]

30:18.690 --> 30:20.799
Hap, I need to see you.

30:24.263 --> 30:27.027
You're still thinking
about Billy, aren't you?

30:28.500 --> 30:31.073
Hap's getting his hooks back in.

30:31.170 --> 30:32.722
I told you.

30:34.673 --> 30:37.246
You told me I was too old and sick

30:37.247 --> 30:39.468
to chase an old grudge.

30:40.479 --> 30:42.699
Well, the doctor says your
heart's getting better.

30:42.881 --> 30:45.716
[Chuckling] I hate to disappoint you.

30:45.784 --> 30:47.217
But...

30:47.286 --> 30:51.455
Hap Briggs can help that boy
a whole lot more than I can.

30:54.626 --> 30:56.860
You once told me Billy was our best shot

30:56.929 --> 30:58.528
at giving Hap a run for his money.

31:00.332 --> 31:03.649
But Billy doesn't have
the capital to take on Hap.

31:04.470 --> 31:06.030
And neither do we.

31:06.205 --> 31:08.296
Maybe it's not just about money.

31:08.640 --> 31:10.907
You're telling me there's
not one person out there

31:10.976 --> 31:12.843
who doesn't hate Hap as much as we do...

31:12.911 --> 31:14.544
and who'd be willing to back Billy?

31:14.613 --> 31:16.646
[Chuckles]

31:16.715 --> 31:19.382
Well, now that you put it that way...

31:20.319 --> 31:22.102
There just might be.

31:22.855 --> 31:25.422
[Chuckles]

31:26.425 --> 31:29.927
You can tell Riyadh, Briggs
is drilling for gas...

31:30.596 --> 31:31.893
Not oil.

31:32.664 --> 31:34.865
There's photos, internal memoranda.

31:34.933 --> 31:36.733
It's all there.

31:38.003 --> 31:39.662
Well done, Ahmed.

31:40.272 --> 31:42.973
Of course, the committee
will need output records

31:43.041 --> 31:44.531
- just to be sure.
- No.

31:45.978 --> 31:47.310
You want anything else on Hap Briggs,

31:47.379 --> 31:49.212
you're gonna have to
let me talk to my son.

31:51.850 --> 31:54.317
That can be arranged.

31:54.386 --> 31:56.319
Now.

31:56.388 --> 31:58.855
♪

32:08.100 --> 32:09.166
You got the pills?

32:09.234 --> 32:10.367
Let me come inside.

32:10.435 --> 32:12.702
Give me the pills, man. [Sniffles]

32:15.073 --> 32:16.439
Easy.

32:18.143 --> 32:20.343
Don't take too many
of those all at once.

32:25.851 --> 32:28.351
[Sighs]

32:28.420 --> 32:30.220
Oh.

32:30.289 --> 32:31.521
[Sighs]

32:32.691 --> 32:34.297
What about the cash?

32:35.027 --> 32:36.737
Oh, great.

32:37.396 --> 32:39.296
I should've seen this coming.

32:39.364 --> 32:43.700
Spinks, the pharmacy, the threats...

32:43.769 --> 32:45.669
Gary, you've done enough damage.

32:45.737 --> 32:48.205
You convinced yourself you
had nothing to do with that?

32:48.273 --> 32:50.974
Maybe it started out as a
way to get back at my father,

32:51.043 --> 32:53.677
but you are the one who
turned it into something else!

32:53.745 --> 32:55.178
You were the one who
turned it into murder!

32:55.247 --> 32:56.813
Because you couldn't
do what had to be done!

32:56.882 --> 32:58.481
Well, now I know what needs to be done!

32:58.550 --> 33:00.750
Come on, Wick, man, we're partners!

33:01.753 --> 33:04.621
Just help me disappear,
and it'll all be over.

33:04.690 --> 33:06.723
[Breathing heavily]

33:06.792 --> 33:08.859
Come on, bro.

33:09.995 --> 33:11.494
There's always another threat.

33:11.563 --> 33:13.230
There's always another cash grab.

33:13.298 --> 33:14.943
There's always another body.

33:17.436 --> 33:20.619
This is the only way
it can truly be done.

33:21.573 --> 33:23.173
- Whoa, whoa.
- Hey, hey.

33:23.241 --> 33:24.274
- No, no!
- You son of a bitch!

33:24.343 --> 33:26.042
You're gonna pay for
what you did to my wife!

33:26.111 --> 33:27.611
- I had nothing to do with that!
- Wick: Shut up!

33:27.679 --> 33:31.348
You need to step outside
and let me handle this.

33:31.416 --> 33:32.416
He killed my son!

33:32.484 --> 33:33.750
He killed my son!

33:33.819 --> 33:36.389
Billy, Billy! One bad
choice, and it never ends.

33:36.390 --> 33:37.488
[Glass shatters]

33:42.895 --> 33:44.141
Gary!

33:46.131 --> 33:48.131
[Knock on door]

33:52.604 --> 33:54.371
Come in.

33:54.439 --> 33:57.240
Please.

34:00.579 --> 34:02.379
[Gary breathing heavily]

34:02.447 --> 34:04.881
[Grunts, groans]

34:04.950 --> 34:06.983
I didn't do nothin'!

34:07.052 --> 34:10.353
I've been told I need to
break this off with you.

34:10.422 --> 34:11.788
By whom?

34:11.857 --> 34:13.723
Your wife.

34:13.792 --> 34:16.092
[Breathing heavily]

34:20.331 --> 34:22.799
So my wife knows we're involved.

34:22.868 --> 34:24.434
Yep.

34:26.204 --> 34:28.186
And you said?

34:28.407 --> 34:30.127
That she was right.

34:32.878 --> 34:37.281
♪

34:37.349 --> 34:39.149
Wick: Gary!

34:46.324 --> 34:49.793
So, you asked me here to what? End it?

34:51.429 --> 34:53.964
I asked you here to talk about Wick.

34:59.071 --> 35:00.770
[Branch snaps]

35:02.274 --> 35:04.407
What about him?

35:08.714 --> 35:09.912
It's like this.

35:27.199 --> 35:29.427
We need to be more careful.

35:36.975 --> 35:38.375
[Grunting]

35:50.389 --> 35:52.022
Whoa, whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

35:52.090 --> 35:53.890
[Breathing heavily]

35:53.959 --> 35:55.025
[Moans]

35:55.093 --> 35:57.027
Oh, my God.

35:57.095 --> 35:59.629
Help me.

35:59.698 --> 36:01.197
- [Sighs]
- [Dialing]

36:01.266 --> 36:02.432
Whoa, what are you doing?

36:02.501 --> 36:04.000
He's hurt, man. We got to call for help.

36:04.069 --> 36:06.136
- What are you talking about?
- Call for...

36:06.204 --> 36:08.780
You wanted him dead, right?

36:09.407 --> 36:12.175
- We leave him here. We walk away.
- Oh, God.

36:12.244 --> 36:14.477
[Grunting]

36:15.614 --> 36:16.946
[Sighing] Oh, God.

36:18.884 --> 36:19.972
Wick.

36:23.086 --> 36:24.100
Wick.

36:24.156 --> 36:27.524
♪

36:31.169 --> 36:34.070
[Talking in distance]

36:36.585 --> 36:38.919
<i>Nurse Carter to Far
West nurses' station.</i>

36:38.987 --> 36:41.822
<i>Nurse Carter, report to
Far West nurses' station.</i>

36:45.594 --> 36:46.722
Hey.

36:47.329 --> 36:48.652
Hey.

36:48.764 --> 36:50.664
Where were you? I was worried.

36:50.732 --> 36:53.500
Oh, I just went outside
for a bit. I needed to...

36:53.569 --> 36:55.469
clear my head.

36:57.139 --> 36:58.939
Billy.

36:59.007 --> 37:00.242
Yeah, sweetheart?

37:02.144 --> 37:04.032
When I told the sheriff who did this...

37:05.314 --> 37:06.923
The look on your face...

37:07.783 --> 37:09.083
it scared me.

37:10.486 --> 37:11.663
Why?

37:12.421 --> 37:14.388
'Cause I know you.

37:14.656 --> 37:17.430
And I know you'd do
anything to protect me.

37:18.794 --> 37:22.389
But please just let the
police handle this one, okay?

37:25.667 --> 37:26.814
Promise me.

37:28.103 --> 37:29.603
Yeah.

37:29.671 --> 37:31.638
I promise.

37:37.613 --> 37:39.546
Hey, Lacey.

37:39.615 --> 37:41.047
We did it. She... she bought it.

37:41.116 --> 37:42.549
She bought all of it.

37:42.618 --> 37:43.618
- Good.
- [Chuckles]

37:43.685 --> 37:45.752
My father will be very pleased.

37:45.821 --> 37:48.021
Even better, I talked to my son.

37:48.090 --> 37:50.257
He's happy. He's... he's safe.

37:50.325 --> 37:51.691
Good.

37:51.760 --> 37:53.619
Lacey, I wanted to...

37:53.996 --> 37:55.565
I want to thank you.

37:56.131 --> 37:58.098
I just... I don't know
what would've happened

37:58.167 --> 38:00.334
if we wouldn't have worked
together on this, you know?

38:00.702 --> 38:01.848
Yeah.

38:03.138 --> 38:04.804
A.J., no, no.

38:04.873 --> 38:06.673
What?

38:06.742 --> 38:08.408
Lacey, but earlier...

38:08.477 --> 38:11.211
Earlier, I got caught up in a moment.

38:11.280 --> 38:14.414
And the last time I did
that, I fell for a liar.

38:14.983 --> 38:18.785
That's not a mistake I'm
gonna make ever again.

38:19.588 --> 38:23.290
♪

38:23.358 --> 38:25.458
[Sighs]

38:30.232 --> 38:32.132
[Clears throat] Hey.

38:34.536 --> 38:35.936
So, I talked to the sheriff.

38:36.005 --> 38:37.804
They're still looking for Gary.

38:38.073 --> 38:40.640
The only lead they got puts him
across town from wre we left him.

38:40.709 --> 38:41.942
Yeah.

38:42.311 --> 38:45.145
If anyone asks, we
went for a walk, okay?

38:45.214 --> 38:46.746
I was a wreck because of the baby,

38:46.815 --> 38:48.448
and you... you tried to console me.

38:50.185 --> 38:51.989
We never turn on each other.

38:53.822 --> 38:56.030
We stay tight. We stay loyal.

38:57.392 --> 38:59.059
We take this to the grave.

38:59.127 --> 39:02.095
[Sighs]

39:02.164 --> 39:04.297
[Exhales deeply]

39:04.366 --> 39:06.166
To the grave.

39:08.837 --> 39:09.869
[Sniffles]

39:09.938 --> 39:11.271
Here.

39:11.340 --> 39:13.073
You need this as much as I do.

39:13.141 --> 39:15.976
♪

39:20.148 --> 39:23.783
♪ Sweetness ♪

39:23.852 --> 39:26.953
♪ I can read your mind ♪

39:29.258 --> 39:34.127
♪ I see your skin turn red ♪

39:34.196 --> 39:35.196
It's over.

39:35.264 --> 39:38.098
♪ When you lie ♪

39:39.801 --> 39:40.967
Good.

39:41.036 --> 39:44.371
♪ If you don't want
to tell me nothing ♪

39:44.439 --> 39:47.907
♪ Then you can go straight to hell ♪

39:47.976 --> 39:50.176
I forgive you.

39:50.245 --> 39:53.446
♪ Now I'm gonna tell you something ♪

39:53.515 --> 39:55.148
Now come to bed with your wife.

39:55.217 --> 39:58.585
♪ You screwed this up yourself ♪

39:58.654 --> 40:01.421
[Telephone ringing]

40:01.690 --> 40:02.690
Woman: Hello?

40:02.724 --> 40:04.457
<i>Clifton: Now, you listen here.</i>

40:04.526 --> 40:07.494
<i>Your boss said that if I
ever have anything for her</i>

40:07.562 --> 40:09.062
<i>to give her a call.</i>

40:09.131 --> 40:10.930
<i>Well, I've got something.</i>

40:10.999 --> 40:12.766
There's this kid up here

40:12.834 --> 40:15.502
who's being crapped on by Hap Briggs.

40:15.570 --> 40:19.806
This is our chance to get
even, but we need her help.

40:19.875 --> 40:21.308
<i>Just a minute.</i>

40:21.376 --> 40:25.211
Ma'am, it's that
Clifton Lundegren again.

40:25.280 --> 40:28.381
He says he has a proposal
you might be interested in.

40:28.450 --> 40:30.317
Something about a kid...

40:30.385 --> 40:33.655
And crushing your ex-husband,
Hap, in the process.

40:34.356 --> 40:36.254
I'll put him through on line one.

